OL,3,CArchaeological 'jigsaw' reveals 2,000-
OL,4,Cyear-old Roman wall paintings in London
OL,6,FAn excavation in London has revealed
OL,7,Fone of the largest collections of
OL,8,Fpainted Roman wall plaster to be
OL,9,Fdiscovered in the capital.
OL,11,FArchaeologists have spent four years
OL,12,Fworking on thousands of fragments of
OL,13,Fshattered plaster discovered at a site
OL,14,Fin Southwark, near London Bridge
OL,15,Fstation and Borough Market, in 2021 to
OL,16,Fpainstakingly piece together the
OL,17,Fartwork of a high-status Roman
OL,18,Fbuilding.
