OL,3,CArchaeological 'jigsaw' reveals 2,000-
OL,4,Cyear-old Roman wall paintings in London
OL,6,FThe paintings ` which display bright
OL,7,Fyellow panel designs with black
OL,8,Fintervals, decorated with beautiful
OL,9,Fimages of birds, fruit, flowers, and
OL,10,Flyres ` demonstrate both the wealth
OL,11,Fand taste of the building's owners,
OL,12,Faccording to the excavation team at
OL,13,Fthe Museum of London Archaeology
OL,14,F(Mola).
OL,16,FYellow panel designs were scarce in
OL,17,Fthe Roman period, and repeating yellow
OL,18,Fpanels found at the site in Southwark
OL,19,Fwere even scarcer, making the
OL,20,Fdiscovery extremely rare.
