OL,3,CArchaeological 'jigsaw' reveals 2,000-
OL,4,Cyear-old Roman wall paintings in London
OL,6,FAmong the fragments is rare evidence
OL,7,Fof a painter's signature ` the first
OL,8,Fknown example of this practice in
OL,9,FBritain.
OL,11,FFramed by a 'tabula ansata', a carving
OL,12,Fof a decorative tablet used to sign
OL,13,Fartwork in the Roman world, it
OL,14,Fcontains the Latin word 'fecit' which
OL,15,Ftranslates to "has made this".
OL,17,FBut the fragment is broken where the
OL,18,Fpainter's name would have appeared,
OL,19,Fmeaning their identity will likely
OL,20,Fnever be known.
