OL,3,CArchaeological 'jigsaw' reveals 2,000-
OL,4,Cyear-old Roman wall paintings in London
OL,6,FUnusual graffiti of the ancient Greek
OL,7,Falphabet has also been reconstructed `
OL,8,Fthe only example of this inscription
OL,9,Ffound to date in Roman Britain.
OL,11,FThe precision of the scored letters
OL,12,Fsuggests that it was done by a
OL,13,Fproficient writer and not someone
OL,14,Fundertaking writing practice.
OL,16,FSome fragments imitate high-status
OL,17,Fwall tiles, such as red Egyptian
OL,18,Fporphyry ` a crystal-speckled volcanic
OL,19,Fstone ` framing the elaborate veins of
OL,20,FAfrican giallo antico ` a yellow
OL,21,Fmarble.
