OL,3,CArchaeological 'jigsaw' reveals 2,000-
OL,4,Cyear-old Roman wall paintings in London
OL,6,F"Many of the fragments were very
OL,7,Fdelicate and pieces from different
OL,8,Fwalls had been jumbled together when
OL,9,Fthe building was demolished, so it was
OL,10,Flike assembling the world's most
OL,11,Fdifficult jigsaw puzzle.
OL,13,F"I was lucky to have been helped by my
OL,14,Fcolleagues in other specialist teams
OL,15,Ffor helping me arrange this titanic
OL,16,Fpuzzle as well as interpret ornaments
OL,17,Fand inscriptions ` including Ian Betts
OL,18,Fand the British School at Rome ` who
OL,19,Fgave me their invaluable opinions and
OL,20,Fresources.
