OL,3,CArchaeological 'jigsaw' reveals 2,000-
OL,4,Cyear-old Roman wall paintings in London
OL,6,F"There was one time that I thought
OL,7,Fthat this fragment goes here, and I
OL,8,Fwoke up and it actually happened ` so
OL,9,Fyou could say I was working a double
OL,10,Fshift.
OL,12,F"But it's a beautiful end result."
OL,14,FOne fragment features the face of a
OL,15,Fcrying woman with a Flavian period (AD
OL,16,F69-96) hairstyle, hinting at the time
OL,17,Fperiod it may have been created.
OL,19,FWork to further explore each piece of
OL,20,Fplaster continues.
